## 4. Visual Dashboard Features

The dashboard is served locally at [http://localhost:8503](http://localhost:8503) and features three key panels:

### A. Officer Feedback Portal
Allows officers to select an active event ticket, input the actual clearance delay, congestion level, and operational outcome, and close the ticket:
* ![Streamlit Feedback Submission Panel](C:/Users/lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/brain/2d2e1604-43c3-41ae-9898-ff5199fa22aa/.system_generated/click_feedback/click_feedback_1781632800719.png)

### B. Ops Control Room Analytics
Contains live Plotly charts comparing predictions against actual outcomes over time, distribution comparisons, and three key metrics:
- **Global Mean Absolute Error (MAE)**: Measures delay deviation in minutes.
- **Classification Accuracy**: Percentage of correct congestion class predictions.
- **Model Drift Index**: Computes:
$$\text{Drift Index} = \text{Global Accuracy} - \text{Recent Accuracy (Last 15)}$$
If this value exceeds $0.10$ (10% drop in recent accuracy), a visual warning is shown in the sidebar.

